&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Community Staff Nurses &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agenda for Change - Band 5 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;District Nursing Service&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rotherham Wide&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for highly motivated and effective team players, committed to providing a high quality nursing service within the District Nursing Service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be a qualified RGN with experience in a community setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please ensure you read the attached job description and person specification to ensure you meet the essential requirements for this position before submitting your application.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;A driving licence and access to a vehicle is essential for this post due to the requirements for regular travel.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post will require the relevant disclosure check with the Criminal Record Bureau.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information or an informal discussion please contact Jill Tideswell on 07919395871.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please apply via NHS Jobs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; using the online application form.  Please note: - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Trust will only accept on-line applications for all vacancies.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;This vacancy will close before the advertised closing date if sufficient applications are received.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Overseas candidates wishing to apply, who would require immigration sponsorship, can self-assess the likelihood of obtaining a Certificate of Sponsorship for the post on the UKBA website.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We reserve the right to close a job advert early where sufficient applications have been received without prior notice. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Rotherham NHS Foundation Trust is committed to equality of opportunity and welcomes applications from everyone regardless of ethnicity, disability, gender, age, faith or sexual orientation. The Trust seeks to establish a workforce as diverse as the population it serves. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; The Trust operates a smoke free policy on all premises and grounds. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; The Trust is committed to supporting a healthy work-life balance. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
